# 2. Clean Up Scanner Warnings (Recommended)

Your scanner currently flags many **false positives** like:


curl https
wget https
bash -i


These appear in documentation files and are **normal**.

Modify your malware scan to ignore common directories:

```bash
grep -R "bash -i" /home \
--exclude-dir=.git \
--exclude-dir=node_modules \
--exclude-dir=.vscode

This improves signal-to-noise ratio.

3. Commit Changes

Run:

git add .

Then:

git commit -m "SYSWATCH PRO security monitoring framework"
4. Push to GitHub
git push origin main
